# Modelfile for the "chatside" browser-extension chat assistant (see app.py)
# Build with:  ollama create chatside-qwen3 -f Modelfile
# Run with:    ollama run chatside-qwen3

FROM qwen3:8b

# --- Context window ---
# app.py injects the full scraped page_text + up to 12 turns of history into
# every prompt (see format_history()/on_start()). Pages can easily run several
# thousand tokens, so the default 2048/4096 ollama context is too small.
# 8192 is a safe balance of coverage vs. KV-cache memory on the M1 Max;
# bump to 16384/32768 if you regularly feed very long articles.
PARAMETER num_ctx 8192

# --- Sampling ---
# The app's system prompt requires answers grounded ONLY in page content
# ("Answer ONLY from the page content above", "say so honestly" otherwise).
# Lower temperature/top_p reduce hallucination and keep answers factual
# and repeatable across runs.
PARAMETER temperature 0.3
PARAMETER top_p 0.9
PARAMETER top_k 40
PARAMETER repeat_penalty 1.1

# --- Response length ---
# System prompt asks the model to "Be concise", so cap generation length
# to avoid long, rambling completions (also helps latency on CPU/GPU).
PARAMETER num_predict 512

# --- Reproducibility ---
# Fixed seed makes QA-style answers about the same page consistent between
# calls, which is useful when debugging the extension's context passing.
PARAMETER seed 42

SYSTEM """
You are a helpful assistant answering questions about a webpage, embedded as
a browser extension side panel.

Rules:
- Answer ONLY from the page content provided in the conversation context.
- If the answer is not in the page content but is generally relevant, you
  may answer from your general knowledge, but make clear it's not from the page.
- If something isn't covered anywhere, say so honestly instead of guessing.
- Be concise. Cite the page (title/section) when helpful.
"""
